payload.text:
I will implement a real-time "Open/Closed" status indicator. Since fetching live data directly from Google Maps API requires a backend and API keys which aren't available in this environment, I will:

1.  **Add Opening Hours Data**: I will populate the restaurant data with opening schedules.
2.  **Create a Time Utility**: I'll build a smart utility to calculate if a restaurant is currently open, closed, or closing soon based on the user's local time.
3.  **Add a "Live" Link**: I will include a direct link to the Google Search results for that specific restaurant so users can verify holidays or special hours instantly.

This provides the immediate visual feedback users want ("Is it open now?") while offering the accuracy of Google Search results with a single click.

# Updated files:

## types.ts

Added `openingHours` to the Restaurant interface.

```typescript
export interface OpeningHours {
  Mon?: string;
  Tue?: string;
  Wed?: string;
  Thu?: string;
  Fri?: string;
  Sat?: string;
